NAME: Brand_Level_Rule_vod
DESCRIPTION: This pricing rule is for defining value-based rebates on a brand level. A brand is represented by the Detail product the order products are associated with. Brand Level rules can utilize scales (quantity, value)

NAME: Discount_Rule_vod
DESCRIPTION: This pricing rule is for defining value-based rebates, also known as discounts. Those can be direct net prices or percentage-based discounts. Discount rules can utilize scales (quantity, value) as well as user overrides.

NAME: Limit_Rule_vod
DESCRIPTION: This pricing rule type is for defining various limits on order quantity or values. Limits can be defined as hard stops or warnings only.

NAME: Free_Goods_Rule_vod
DESCRIPTION: This pricing rule is for defining free goods-based rebates, also known as natural rebates. Free goods rules can utilize scales (quantity, value) as well as user overrides.

NAME: List_Price_Rule_vod
DESCRIPTION: This pricing rule type is for defining the list price of an order product (SKU). A valid list price rule needs to exist for a product to appear during order entry.

NAME: Product_Group_Level_Rule_vod
DESCRIPTION: This pricing rule is for defining value-based rebates on a product group level. A product group is defined through the product catalog entry of the same name and the underlying order products. Product Group rules can utilize scales (quantity, value).
